Describing commitments in precise terms ensures signatory states understand the limits of their obligations , and prevents self-serving or opportunistic behavior in the future .
Harder laws include demands or obligations with which signatory states must comply .
In contrast , softer laws typically list a number of things signatory states are permitted to do within the confines of the agreement , but do not require them to do anything in particular .
If the agreement includes promises from signatory states to investigate an issue or conduct feasibility studies within a period of time , but does not require the implementation of any concrete measures , these are soft law provisions .
Harder laws typically delegate the authority for interpretation of the agreement to an independent third body , while softer laws leave interpretation up to signatory states .

The completed square shows every possible way a child could inherit this gene , and what the chances are for each result .
The Punnett square shows us the likelihood of creating children with certain genes .
Add up the chance of each square with one or more dominant alleles to get the chance that the child expresses the dominant trait .
Add up the chance of each square with two recessive alleles to get the chance that the child expresses the recessive trait .
In our example , there are two squares with at least one F , so each child has a 50 % chance to have black fur .
There are two squares with ff , so each child has a 50 % chance to have yellow fur .

Note that the carrying value of the business is not necessarily equal to the market value ( also known as fair value ) of the business , or what the market would be willing to pay .
A business may be willing to pay more than the carrying value because the business in question may have great profit margins , exceptional future profit growth prospects , or a major competitive advantage .
This would mean the carrying value is equal to $ 1 million ( $ 2 million of tangible assets minus $ 1 million of liabilities ) .
Assume the carrying value of Company B is $ 500,000 .
Since goodwill is equal to the amount the purchase exceeds the carrying value , the goodwill in this case would equal $ 500,000 .
This simply means that if you subtract the business 's assets from their liabilities to get a carrying value , and you determine what the market would pay in theory for those assets , the result in this case would be $ 1 million .

For example , a 40 year old man 's MHR would be 180 , and his fat burning zone would be between 108 and 126 beats per minute .
The fat burning zone is defined as the activity level at which your body is burning primarily fat for energy .
If weight loss is the goal of your workout , then finding your fat burning zone and maintaining your workout in that zone may maximize the amount of fat you burn .
The fat burning zone is different for everybody , but can be helpful when you 're working out to help you adjust the intensity of your workout based on your heart rate .
This information can then be used to determine at what heart rate level you are burning the most fat and calories in your fat burning zone .
This is the least technical of all the ways to determine your fat burning zone .
Calculate your fat burning zone with a formula .
Heart rate monitors can help you accurately see where your heart rate is and based on your age , height and weight can also determine your fat burning zone .
By using a heart rate monitor you 're going to get a more accurate idea of where your fat burning zone is .
This is because the heart rate monitor will calculate your heart rate as you exercise and will then use your actual heart rate information to calculate your fat burning zone .
Include activities that are moderate-intensity and will fall into your fat burning zone about half of the time .
However , total calories burned also depends on the duration of a workout and it may be easier to do a longer work out in the fat burning zone as it 's at a lower intensity .
If you 're interested in your fat burning zone and how you can best utilize that information , meeting with a personal trainer or coach may be a good option .
They can help you find your fat burning zone and help design an appropriate workout that utilizes that information .
Also ask how you can utilize your fat burning zone to your best advantage .
This may help you tailor not only your fat burning zone , but give you the tools and data to help you reach that particular zone in any given workout .

Building a form - You will need to use a form to build your artificial rock since concrete is very heavy .
Sculpting the concrete - Use a point trowel to sculpt the concrete after applying to the form .
Texturing the concrete - Use a sea sponge to create a pock marked , weathered effect .
Curing the concrete - Concrete takes a full month to cure and is about 75 % cured after the first week .
Scraping the concrete - Wait a minimum of 3 full days of curing before commencing this stage .
Washing the concrete - Wash the rock thoroughly before proceeding to add color .
Painting the concrete - Using spray bottles and water based paints you will mist multiple layers of complementary colors over and over again to create a deep and realistic rock color .
Sealing the concrete - Use water based concrete sealant and apply 3 layers allowing time to dry completely between .
Mixing concrete - This is done in a bucket by hand or with a point trowel , or in a wheel barrow with a pointed shovel , OR on a piece of plywood with a square head shovel OR in a cement mixer .
